           Root Cause:    PostgreSQL Deployment uses an emptyDir volume with sizeLimit:8Gi on node dev-worker-0 which has only ~7.9 GiB allocatable ephemeral storage. As PostgreSQL writes WAL segments, data pages, and log files, the kubelet will trigger pod eviction before the declared sizeLimit is reached, causing an imminent DiskPressure condition. The node's /var filesystem (XFS, /dev/vda4) already shows a ~1.7 GiB drop in 30 minutes around deployment time. The fix requires migrating from emptyDir to a PersistentVolumeClaim (LVMS/TopoLVM available), and since ArgoCD manages this Deployment, the change must be applied via GitOps.
